            <div type="translation">
                <p><lb n="1"/>Verses 1-2 not usefully translated. 
                      <lb n="2"/>Verses 3-4: And now they see the creator being taken up, He whom [only] the angels are accustomed to see (after <ptr target="Ševčenko2012"/>, 75)</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Probably, second half of an epigram dedicated to the Ascension, which continues from the northern respond (<ref target="MedCY.044.021.html">MedCY.044.021</ref>). Because of the state of preservation, the division between the verses is uncertain (<ptr target="#Ševčenko2012"/>, 75). Only the last two verses (lines 7-13) are understandable. The source of the epigram has not been identified.</p>
            </div>
